HJR259 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3 OBSERVING MILITARY APPRECIATION DAY AND HONORING MEMBERS OF
4 THE 99TH AIR REFUELING SQUADRON AND THE 117TH AIR REFUELING
5 WING.
6
7 WHEREAS, the Alabama Legislature proudly observes
8 Military Appreciation Day each year to recognize and honor
9 the extraordinary service and sacrifice of the men and women
10 who serve in the United States Armed Forces, including those
11 on active duty, in the National Guard and Reserve, and those
12 who have previously served the nation as veterans; and
13 WHEREAS, the people of Alabama maintain a deep and
14 enduring relationship with the United States military, as
15 the state is home to military installations including
16 Redstone Arsenal, Anniston Army Depot, Sumpter Smith Joint
17 National Guard Base, Maxwell Air Force Base, Dannelly Field,
18 Fort Rucker, the United States Coast Guard Aviation Training
19 Center, Fort McClellan Training Center, the Alabama National
20 Guard Joint Force Headquarters, and numerous additional
21 military units and organizations that contribute to our
22 national security; and
23 WHEREAS, Alabama is home to nearly 400,000 veterans,
24 13,500 active-duty service members, 26,700 National Guard
25 and Reserve members, and 50,000 military spouses and
26 dependents, all of whom contribute to the strength and
27 resilience of our communities and our nation; and
28 WHEREAS, these brave individuals serve around the
Page 1

WHEREAS, these brave individuals serve around the
HJR259 Enrolled
29 world defending freedom, preserving peace, and protecting
30 the security of the United States and its allies; and
31 WHEREAS, on March 12, 2026, members of the 99th Air
32 Refueling Squadron tragically lost their lives during combat
33 operations in service to the United States, demonstrating
34 the ultimate sacrifice in defense of freedom and the safety
35 of our nation; and
36 WHEREAS, the fallen airmen, Major John Alex Klinner,
37 Captain Ariana Savino, and Technical Sergeant Ashley Pruitt,
38 served their nation with honor, courage, and devotion to
39 duty, embodying the highest traditions of the United States
40 Air Force; and
41 WHEREAS, the members of the Legislature join the
42 people of this state in honoring the courage, commitment,
43 and sacrifice of these fallen service members and extend our
44 deepest condolences to their families, loved ones, fellow
45 airmen, and the entire 99th Air Refueling Squadron; and
46 WHEREAS, the members of the 99th Air Refueling
47 Squadron serve as a fully integrated force with the 117th
48 Air Refueling Wing at Sumpter Smith Joint National Guard
49 Base in Birmingham, Alabama, working hand-in-hand with
50 Alabama National Guard personnel as part of a unified
51 mission, and the "Vulcan Refuelers" are regarded as an
52 enduring part of Alabama's military family; now therefore,
53 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
54 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That the Legislature hereby
55 recognizes March 19, 2026, as Military Appreciation Day and
56 expresses its profound gratitude to all members of the
Page 2

expresses its profound gratitude to all members of the
HJR259 Enrolled
57 United States Armed Forces, past and present, for their
58 honorable service to our nation.
59 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, That the Alabama Legislature
60 solemnly honors the memory and sacrifice of Major John Alex
61 Klinner, Captain Ariana Savino, and Technical Sergeant
62 Ashley Pruitt of the 99th Air Refueling Squadron, who lost
63 their lives on March 12, 2026, recognizing their bravery and
64 devotion to duty as an enduring example of service above
65 self.
66 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, That the Legislature extends
67 its heartfelt sympathies and prayers to the families of
68 these fallen airmen, the members of the 99th Air Refueling
69 Squadron, the members of the 117th Air Refueling Wing, and
70 the entire United States Air Force community.
71 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, That a copy of this
72 resolution be delivered to the command leadership of the
73 99th Air Refueling Squadron at Sumpter Smith Joint National
74 Guard Base, the Alabama National Guard, and the families of
75 the fallen airmen as a token of the Legislature's highest
76 respect and appreciation.
